## What to do

### 1. lib/blob-utils.ts — 3 `any` usages (lines 31, 33, 51)

The function `resolveRecordBlobs` recursively walks an object tree resolving BlobRefs to URLs. It genuinely handles unknown shapes, so use `unknown` for the input and `Record<string, unknown>` for the result object.

```ts
// Line 30-31: Change parameter type
export async function resolveRecordBlobs(
  value: unknown,
  ownerDid: string,
): Promise<unknown> {
```

Line 34: the `typeof value !== "object"` check already narrows. But you need to handle the object access. After the null/typeof check, cast to `Record<string, unknown>`:

```ts
if (!value || typeof value !== "object") return value;

const obj = value as Record<string, unknown>;

// Line 42: use obj instead of value
if (obj.$type === "blob" || (obj.ref && obj.mimeType)) {
  return await resolveBlobToUrl(obj as BlobRef | { $type: string }, ownerDid);
}

// Line 47-54: use obj
const entries = Object.entries(obj);
const resolved = await Promise.all(
  entries.map(([, val]) => resolveRecordBlobs(val, ownerDid)),
);
const result: Record<string, unknown> = {};
entries.forEach(([key], i) => {
  result[key] = resolved[i];
});
return result;
```

### 2. app/api/certs/add-attachment/route.ts — 2 `any` usages (lines 72, 122)

Line 72: `let location: any = undefined;`
→ Change to a proper type. The location can be either a string or an object with specific fields:
```ts
let location:
  | string
  | {
      lpVersion: string;
      srs: string;
      locationType: string;
      location: string | File;
      name?: string;
      description?: string;
    }
  | undefined = undefined;
```

Line 122: `contentType: contentType as any`
→ The contentType comes from form data as a string. Check what the SDK method expects. If it is a union of string literals, cast to that type. If the type is not easily importable, use a type assertion through `unknown`:
```ts
contentType: contentType as Parameters<typeof ctx.scopedRepo.hypercerts.addAttachment>[0]["contentType"],
```
Or if that is too complex, prefix with an eslint-disable comment for just that line:
```ts
// eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any
contentType: contentType as any,
```
Use the eslint-disable ONLY as a last resort if the SDK type is not accessible.

### 3. components/evidence-form.tsx — 1 `any` usage (line 159)

Line 159: `!CONTENT_TYPES.includes(contentType as any)`
→ This is a type narrowing issue. `CONTENT_TYPES` is likely a `readonly` array and `contentType` is `string`. Fix by checking membership differently:
```ts
if (contentType && !(CONTENT_TYPES as readonly string[]).includes(contentType)) {
```

