Review of hypercerts-mrb.3 found: In `queries/hypercerts/use-contributor-profiles-query.ts` lines 30-35, a new `Map<string, BlueskyProfile>` is constructed unconditionally on every render. Because the Map is a new object reference each render, any component that receives `profileMap` as a prop will re-render even when the underlying data has not changed. This is a performance regression that worsens with the number of contributors.

Evidence: `use-contributor-profiles-query.ts` lines 30-35:
```ts
const profileMap = new Map<string, BlueskyProfile>();
queries.forEach((q, i) => {
  if (q.isSuccess && q.data) {
    profileMap.set(uniqueDids[i], q.data);
  }
});
```

Fix: wrap the Map construction in `useMemo` keyed on `queries` (or on the serialised success data). Example:
```ts
const profileMap = useMemo(() => {
  const map = new Map<string, BlueskyProfile>();
  queries.forEach((q, i) => {
    if (q.isSuccess && q.data) map.set(uniqueDids[i], q.data);
  });
  return map;
}, [queries, uniqueDids]);
```
Note: `uniqueDids` itself should also be memoised (or derived inside the same memo) to avoid the memo invalidating on every render.

Review of hypercerts-mrb.2 found: In `lib/contributor-utils.ts`, `isContributorIdentity` (line 22) checks for an `identity` string field, and `isStrongRef` (line 42) checks for `uri` + `cid` string fields. These are structurally disjoint, which is correct. However, the `isContributorRole` guard (line 32) only checks for a `role` string field — it would also match any arbitrary object that happens to have a `role` property (e.g. a future schema extension). More critically, the `parseContributor` function (line 79) falls through to `String(rawIdentity)` for the third union arm `{ $type: string }`. At runtime, if the AT Protocol SDK returns a typed object with an unknown $type (e.g. a future variant), the identity will be serialised as `[object Object]`, which is then rendered in the UI and potentially used as a Bluesky profile lookup key.

Evidence: `lib/contributor-utils.ts` lines 85-92:
```ts
if (isContributorIdentity(rawIdentity)) {
  identity = rawIdentity.identity;
} else if (isStrongRef(rawIdentity)) {
  identityRef = rawIdentity;
  identity = extractDidFromAtUri(rawIdentity.uri);
} else {
  identity = String(rawIdentity);  // ← produces "[object Object]" for unknown typed objects
}
```

Fix: in the fallback branch, check if `rawIdentity` has a `$type` field and log a warning; set `identity` to an empty string or a safe sentinel rather than `String(rawIdentity)`. Also add a `$type` discriminant check to `isContributorIdentity` and `isContributorRole` to make them more precise (check `$type` starts with `org.hypercerts.claim.activity#`).

## Files
